, 2020}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Endorsements box\n| title = Jacob Hornberger\n| list =\n;Party officials\n* [[John A. Buttrick]], attorney and former chairman of the [[Libertarian Party of Arizona]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/Hornberger2020/posts/169523401163081|title=Endorsement From Judge John A. Buttrick|website=Facebook|last1=Buttrick|first1=John A.}}</ref>\n* Todd Hagopian, businessman and Chair of the Tulsa, OK chapter of the [[Libertarian Party of Oklahoma]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/ToddHagopian/status/1213250283465322497 |title=I would like to formally endorse Jacob Hornberger (@JacobforLiberty) for the Libertarian Presidential Nomination, I believe Jacob is the \"Ron Paul\" Libertarian that we have been seeking & I am proud to offer him my full support, A Campaign of Principle!http://jacobforliberty.com |date=January 3, 2020}}</ref>\n\n;Individuals\n* [[Scott Horton (radio host)|Scott Horton]], radio host and anti-war activist<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bnzV3Gowi0g |title=Horton Hears a Hornberger |date=December 5, 2019 |access-date=December 9, 2019 |via=YouTube.com}}</ref>\n*Jake Porter, nominee for [[Governor]] of [[Iowa]] in [[2018 Iowa gubernatorial election|2018]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://twitter.com/jakedporter/status/1203285843953246209 |title=I had a nice conversation with Jacob Hornberger a couple of days ago and I have decided to join his campaign and support him for the Libertarian Party Presidential nomination. |date=December 7, 2019 |access-date=December 9, 2019 |via=Twitter.com}}</ref>\n* [[Thomas Woods|Tom Woods]], historian and author<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fFbqaTABz7U |title=Ep. 1540 The Horton/Woods Liberty Battle Plan |website=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n* Dave Smith, comedian and podcaster<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oBSMRIaCIWU |title=Part Of The Problem #514 \u2013 Revolution 2.0 With Scott Horton |website=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\n\n;Organizat