secret2/2020-green-and-libertarian-primary-polling?authuser=4 |title=2020 Green and Libertarian Primary Polling |date=March 17, 2019 |publisher=Third Party Watch}}</ref>\n| 730 Registered Libertarian Voters\n| March 10\u201314, 2019\n| \u2013<!--Abramson-->\n| \u2013<!--Armstrong-->\n| \u2013<!--Behrman-->\n| \u2013<!--Blevins-->\n| \u2013<!--Chafee-->\n| \u2013<!--Faas-->\n| \u2013<!--Hornberger-->\n| \u2013 <!--Jorgensen-->\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''33.97%<!--Kokesh-->'''\n| 20.82%<!--McAfee-->\n| \u2013<!--Monds-->\n| \u2013<!--Robb-->\n| \u2013<!--Ruff-->\n| {{party shading/Libertarian}}| '''42.74%<!--Seder-->'''\n| 2.05%<!--Supreme-->\n| 0.41%<!--Vohra-->\n| \u2013<!--Whitney-->\n|  <small>N/A<br /></small>\n|}\n\n=== Online straw polls ===\nThe following are early unofficial online polls that have included various speculative and potential candidates, including some that are not members of the Libertarian Party.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:small;\"\n|-\n! style=\"font-size:88%\"|<small>Poll source</small>\n! style=\"font-size:88%\"|<small>Date(s)</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Justin Amash|Amash]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Tom Campbell (California politician)|Campbell]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''Ince'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Zoltan Istvan|Istvan]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Gary Johnson|Johnson]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Steve Kerbel|Kerbel]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Adam Kokesh|Kokesh]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[John McAfee|McAfee]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Jeffrey Miron|Miron]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Rand Paul|Paul]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Darryl W. Perry|Perry]]'''</small>\n| style=\"font-size:88%\"| <small>'''[[Austin Petersen|Petersen]]'''</sma