20.com/ John Monds for President]\n*[https://www.samrobb2020.com/ Sam Robb for President]\n*[https://verminsupreme.com/ Vermin Supreme for President]\n*[https://www.markwhitney.com/ Mark Whitney for President]\n*[https://www.votevohra.com/ Arvin Vohra for President]\n\n{{United States presidential election, 2020}}\n{{U.S. presidential primaries}}\n{{Libertarian Party (United States)}}\n\n[[Category:Libertarian Party (United States)|Presidential primaries, 2020]]\n[[Category:2020 United States presidential primaries]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Series of electoral contests}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2020 Libertarian Party presidential primaries\n| country = United States\n| type = primary\n| ongoing = yes\n| party_name = no\n| previous_year = [[2016 Libertarian Party presidential primaries|2016]]\n| election_date = January 11 to June 16, 2020\n| next_election = \n| next_year = ''2024''\n| votes_for_election = \n| image1 = [[File:Jacob Hornberger by Gage Skidmore (cropped) (2).jpg|x160px]]\n| candidate1 = Jacob Hornberger\n| color1 = DAA520\n| home_state1 = [[Virginia]]\n| states_carried1 = 5{{efn|No preference received the most votes in North Carolina. Hornberger, the candidate who had received the most votes, was not recognized as the winner.}}\n| popular_vote1 = 8,805\n| percentage1 = 21.77%\n\n| image2 = [[File:Vermin Supreme August 2019 (cropped).jpg|x160px]]\n| candidate2 = [[Vermin Supreme]]\n| color2 = fb9bc2\n| home_state2 = [[Massachusetts]]\n| states_carried2 = 2{{efn|No preference received the most votes in Massachusetts. Supreme, the candidate who had received the most votes, was recognized as the winner by the Secretary of State.}}\n| popular_vote2 = 4,047\n| percentage2 = 10.01%\n\n| image3 = <div style=\"width:115px;\"><span style=\"line-height:150px; vertical-align:center; text-align:center; color:{{Libertarian Party (United States)/meta/color}}; font-size:30px;\"> '''JJ'''</span></div> <!-