 county, 2020.svg|thumb|right|340px|County results \u2014North Carolina.\n----\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{legend|#000000|None of the above}}\n{{legend|#666666|Tie}}\n{{legend|#fb9bc2|Vermin Supreme}}\n{{legend|#F0E68C|Ken Armstrong}}\n{{legend|#800066|Jedidiah Hill}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{legend|#ff7102|Dan Behrman}}\n{{legend|#BA55D3|Jo Jorgensen}}\n{{legend|#214478|Steve Richey}}\n{{legend|#88aa00|Kim Ruff}}\n{{legend|#d0d0d0|No votes}}\n{{col-end}}]]\n{{col-end}}\n\n=== Missouri primary ===\n\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-3}}\n{| class=\"infobox bordered\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"margin:1em 1em 1em 0; font-size:12px; text-align:right; float:none; clear:none;\"\n|-  style=\"background:#e9e9e9; text-align:center;\"\n! colspan=\"3\" | [[2020 United States presidential election in Missouri#Libertarian primary|Missouri Libertarian presidential primary, March 10, 2020]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kmbc.com/article/missouri-primary-joe-biden-donald-trump-win-presidental-preferential-primary/31357212|title=Joe Biden, Donald Trump win Missouri Presidential Preferential Primary |work=KMBC |date=March 10, 2020 |access-date=March 10, 2020}}</ref>\n|-  style=\"background:#e9e9e9; text-align:center;\"\n! style=\"width:200px; vertical-align:middle;\"| Candidate\n! style=\"width:75px; vertical-align:middle;\"| Votes\n! style=\"width:75px; vertical-align:middle;\"| Percentage\n|- style=\"background:#ffef99;\"\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| '''Jacob Hornberger'''\n|'''1,683'''\n| '''74.6%'''\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left;\"| Uncommitted\n|573\n|25.4%\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#eee;\"\n| style=\"margin-right:0.50px\"| '''Total'''\n| style=\"margin-right:0.50px\"| '''2,256 '''\n| style=\"margin-right:0.50px\"| '''100%'''\n|}\n{{col-3}}\n\n[[File:Missouri Libertarian presidential primary election results by county, 2020.svg|thumb|right|340px|County results \u2014Missouri.\n----\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n{{legend|#DAA520|Jacob Hornberger}}\n{{legend|#000000|Uncommitted}}\n{{legend|#666666|